A check of the facts shows that Iowa had one of the country's lowest

Our ruling

   Whitver said unemployment in Iowa was among the lowest in the country
   before the U.S. deliberately shutdown parts of the economy to mitigate the
   spread of COVID-19, and that companies were struggling to find workers.

Iowa unemployment had been at a historic low since 2017, and in February
   it ranked 11th in the country.
